author: Inside Edition
description: It's a device meant to help law enforcement protect themselves against violence on the job, but an Associated Press investigation poses the question of whether or not it's being used properly, particularly by ICE agents. The AP interviewed people who say they were restrained in the WRAP when not displaying violent behavior. Some complaints go back as far as 2020. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: AP Investigates ICE Agents' Use Of Full Body Restraints

author: Inside Edition
description: The parents of the teacher who was stabbed 23 times but her death ruled a suicide are speaking out Wednesday. Ellen Greenberg, 27, was found dead 14 years ago, and her parents have been fighting all that time to have the case reopened. On Tuesday, a medical examiner announced that she's standing by the controversial ruling that Greenberg took her own life. Greenberg's parents say there is ample evidence that she did not commit suicide, including unexplained bruises on her body.
title: Ellen Greenberg's Parents Speak Out After Repeat Suicide Ruling

author: Inside Edition
description: A lithium-ion battery burst into flames after a dog gnawed at it. Fire officials in Chapel Hill, North Carolina, say the family had charged the battery and left it unplugged on a counter. When they were out, Colton the dog went counter-surfing, grabbed the battery and started chewing. David Sasser is Colton's owner and he's also the assistant fire chief. He spoke with Inside Edition. Luckily, mischief-maker Colton is fine.
title: Lithium-Ion Battery Bursts Into Flames After Dog Chews On It

author: Inside Edition
description: AI technology is being used in all sorts of ways, but it comes with a warning. Many on social media are using AI to prank their families, making it look like someone is inside their home. Joe Mele sent his wife an AI-generated video of a sexy maid cleaning the house. Phoebe Adams pranked her boyfriend by texting him that a hunky plumber was fixing their toilet. Now, police are saying fake images could lead to real problems.
title: Police Issue Warning About Using AI To Pull Pranks

author: Inside Edition
description: The new Hulu series about the notorious Murdaugh murders has sparked strong reaction from Alex Murdaugh's attorney. Dick Harpootlian defended Murdaugh at his trial in 2023 for the murder of his wife, Maggie, and son, Paul. The trial captivated the nation. Murdaugh was found guilty and sentenced to life in prison. "Murdaugh: Death in the Family," tells the story of the powerful South Carolina legal dynasty as they spiral toward the fateful night. Harpootlian says the series took a lot of artistic license.
title: Alex Murdaugh's Attorney Speaks Out About New Hulu Series

author: Inside Edition
description: Halloween is a couple weeks away and what's really scary this year are candy prices. Candy prices are up 8% compared to last year. Half of Americans say they're cutting back on candy this Halloween. Inside Edition's Ann Mercogliano has tips on how to save some money on candy this holiday. First: skip candy and hand out snacks like pretzels and cookies. You can also buy store brands as they're usually cheaper. And buy in bulk.
title: Tips On How To 'Trick-or-Treat' Without Breaking The Bank

author: Inside Edition
description: It's being called the most teary-eyed night ever on 'Dancing With The Stars." Fan favorite Robert Irwin dedicated his modern dance performance to his mother Terri, who raised him as a single mom after the death of his famous father, Steve Irwin. During the performance, the camera panned around Robert and his dance partner switched places with his mom. Robert hugged her tightly and broke down in tears.
title: Robert Irwin Dedicates 'Dancing With The Stars' Performance To His Mom

author: Inside Edition
description: An animal sanctuary in Australia announced the births of two new residents, but what are they? Muppets? They're actually tawny frogmouth chicks, but don't worry if you mistake them for a stuffed toy or a dust bunny. Although unusual-looking, zookeepers say they're still cute. Inside Edition Digital’s Mara Montalbano has more.
title: 2 Muppet-Looking Chicks Hatch At Sanctuary In Australia

description: Ellen Greenberg was stabbed more than 20 times, yet her death was ruled a suicide.
title: Medical Examiner's Shocking Ruling In Ellen Greenberg Death #shorts
